verses.text:
There's a silence in God's mercy, Like the softness of the day;
And he speaks to the restless, In the twilight's gentle way;
There's a place where earthly sorrow All can find full rest from care,
And the heart that once was heavy Is now resting sweetly there.

There is mercy with salvation, There is healing in his blood;
There are peace and consolation From the ever-living good;
But the heart of the Sa- vior lies in comfort with his King,
And the weary, as he saves it, All their suffering doth bring.

chorus.text:
He is calling, "Come unto me, Lord, I gladly go," I say;
I will go unto altar,
Everything to Jesus bring.
